		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">strat wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">hee hee hee, is Cheetah Men 2 allowed?</div><br /><br />I don't think so; it's about <em>game</em>-breaking glitches, and it's debatable whether or not Cheetah Men 2 counts as a real game <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" />.<br /><br />I actually had something happen in Castlevania 1 once while playing it in an emulator where it froze and there were attribute glitches all over the place. It was either in Nintendulator or FCEUXD, and I believe it was when I was going through a door (so the screen wasn't scrolling). I assume it wasn't related to emulator inaccuracy (though I could certainly be wrong), but it rules out the typical game crash you get on a real NES. I figure it's some sort of bug.

		

